definitions.definition: A small , slender piece of wood or cardboard serving as a component of a match .
examples: A piece of wood or cardboard becomes a matchstick once the end has been dipped in a sulfurous compound to turn it into a complete match.

definitions.definition: Any similarly small and thin piece.
examples: The explosion blew the powder shed to matchsticks .

main_definition: A small , slender piece of wood or cardboard serving as a component of a match .
secondary_definitions: ( chiefly in the plural ) Any similarly small and thin piece.
